    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-09-12T09:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-09-12T09:30:00-05:00" n="911"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d911">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">831.00/9–1247: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Maleady</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-09-12T10:00:00-04:30"
                            >September 12, 1947—10 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>363. All Caracas barracks and those La Guaira area alerted early this a.m., as
                    were presumably all others throughout country. Traffic being rerouted in all
                    streets adjacent Caracas <hi rend="italic">cuartels</hi>. Military guards are
                    dressed full equipment. Radio stations under guard. Armored and other military
                    cars in evidence all downtown streets. Approximately twelve well-known civilians
                    including Director Geology in Ministry of Fomento, Victor Lopez, arrested.</p>
                <p>Some informants state show military force made intentionally by administration in
                    Junta to impress populace and prevent attempt break up meeting here at which
                        Gallegos’<note n="21" xml:id="d911fn1">Romulo Gallegos, candidate of the
                        governing Junta.</note> presidential candidacy to be publicly proclaimed
                    tonight. Others feel alert occasioned by matter mentioned <gloss
                        target="#t_mytel1">mytel</gloss> 361, September 11, 4 p.m.<note n="22"
                        xml:id="d911fn2">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Reports of uprisings at various places outside Caracas wholly unconfirmed.</p>
                <p>Miraflores Palace source states situation under control and has promised furnish
                    me full details this noon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Maleady</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
